Given that the Earth’s redox landscape changed along with daylength through geological time, we studied the sensitivity of daylength-driven diel Corg burial to reductant and O2 availability in the water column. Diel O2 export and Corg burial fluxes increased with daylength across all O2 boundary conditions (Fig. 2). Increasing O2 in the water column had a strong enhancing effect on Raero and negative effect on O2 export fluxes. For the diel Corg burial rate, determined by both Raero and Ranaero, the effect of O2 levels in the water column was variable (Extended Data Fig. 3). Depending on the inhibition strength of O2 on Ranaero, Corg burial either increases or decreases with the O2 boundary conditions. Given that Ranaero is O2 sensitive, the negative impact of pO2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
